When a user attempts to load a page with page restrictions that prevent that user from viewing the page, they see the following text (also see attached screenshot):
{quote}
h3. You cannot view this page
Page level restrictions have been applied that limit access to this page.
{quote}

However, when the include macro is used to include the same page, the following error is presented upon a red background (again, see screenshot):
{quote}
Unable to render \{include\} Couldn't find a page to include called: restricted
{quote}
This error message is technically incorrect, as the page "restricted" does exist, though it cannot be shown. The reported error in this scenario should be changed to better reflect the reality of the situation.

